{"questionId":"9076456","questionHtml":"<p>Show that the final volume of the gas is about 53 m<sup>3</sup>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong>Using&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{V_1}}}{{{T_1}}} = \\frac{{{V_2}}}{{{T_2}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>V</mi>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>V</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>T</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><em>V</em><sub>2</sub> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{47.1 \\times (273 + 19)}}{{(273 - 12)}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>47.1</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n      <mn>273</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>19</mn>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n      <mn>273</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><em>V</em><sub>2</sub> = 52.7&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>m<sup>3</sup><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 2</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong>Using&nbsp;<em>PV</em> = <em>nRT</em><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p><em>V</em> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{243 \\times 8.31 \\times (273 + 19)}}{{11.2 \\times {{10}^3}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>243</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>8.31</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n      <mn>273</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>19</mn>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>11.2</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><em>V</em> = 52.6&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>m<sup>3</sup><strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076456","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ2.a","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Show that the final volume of the gas is about 53 m3.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)","B.2 – Thermodynamics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}